biography:
Everyone has a story to tell. 
Tag #ShotoniPhone to take part.

Tag #ShotoniPhone to take part.

node.text:
Commissioned by Apple. A peek behind the scenes as Michel Gondry turns a carton of eggs into a dozen pieces of cinema with #iPhone13Pro 🥚 “I like to start with something very trivial and mundane, and find a way to get magic out of it.” #ShotoniPhone by Michel Gondry. @michelgondry

Follow @apple to see more.

Commissioned by Apple. One missing painting. Six Suspects. Watch Whodunnit, shot entirely in Cinematic mode on the new #iPhone13.

#ShotoniPhone by JB Braud @jbbraud

node.title: Shot on iPhone 13 in Cinematic mode

node.text: Commissioned by Apple. “I came up with the idea for my film in a nightmare. I always get my ideas from nightmares. It sounds a bit grim, but it’s not. I just think about what could be happening in a different universe.” #ShotoniPhone by AhaNah C. @vio.waxdrops, Student.

Commissioned by Apple. “I want to see a joyful piece with black men in it because we’re seeing way too much pain in the media and the news. I wanted to create something that would be a much-needed pause from everything that’s happening. I want joy.” #ShotoniPhone by Ciara Z. @ciara.zo, Student.

node.title: Our Light Shines Through the Dark

node.text: Commissioned by Apple. “Making this film was a fantastic feeling. I don’t care about anything else in the world. This is what I want to do.” #ShotoniPhone by Guillermo M., Student.

Commissioned by Apple. “There’s no excuse for anybody not to be making films at this point. It’s a way people can tell their stories and keep them living forever.” #ShotoniPhone by Niko B. @mylifeismundane, Student.

Commissioned by Apple. “We wanted to push the #iPhone12Pro with its Dolby Vision and low-light recording capabilities to the limit.”

#ShotoniPhone 12 Pro by Donghoon J. and James T. of @InciteDesign. 

Music: “RADIANCE” by LORN. 

Head to Stories to see how it was made.

“The unfinished work of racial justice and equality call us all to account. Things must change, and Apple's committed to being a force for that change. Today, I'm proud to announce Apple’s Racial Equity and Justice Initiative, with a $100 million commitment.” Tim Cook

node.title: Apple is taking action to fight systemic racism.

node.text: Commissioned by Apple. Photographer Petecia Le Fawnhawk @Lefawnhawk is known for creating striking surrealist landscapes using a mix of sculpture and editing techniques. Watch to learn about Petecia's creative connection with the desert and how she uses perspective to explore her sense of place in the world. #IWD #ShotoniPhone 11 Pro.

Commissioned by Apple. Fifty miles from Las Vegas, Nevada rests the remains of a prehistoric geological event. Carved by 200 million years of wind. An ocean of rock, a Valley of Fire. 
See how iPhone 11 Pro captured otherworldly imagery using the Ultra Wide camera in this deep dive into another world. 
#ultrawide #ShotoniPhone 11 Pro by Tyler F. @tylerfairbank
Music: “Frontier” by @holly_herndon

Commissioned by Apple. "I walk on the beach every day looking for things to photograph. You get to know the rocks. You have you almost a relationship with your space. And when you change perspective in a way you’re changing the nature of the relationship. And that’s super interesting to me.” #ShotoniPhone by Paul M. @paulmacphail and Scottie C. @scottie_cameron 
Music: “The Immense Endless Belt of Faces” by @elikeszler and “Eighteenth” by @correcreative

Commissioned by Apple. Follow pro snowboarders Red Gerard @redgerard, Danny Davis @travelindan, Kimmy Fasani @kimmyfasani, and Ben Ferguson @ben_ferguson as they explore untouched powder in the backcountry of Interior British Columbia at the legendary Baldface Lodge. #ShotoniPhone by Joe C. @carlinojoevideo

node.text:
Swipe to spot these masters of disguise from the Bornean rainforests.

Commissioned by Apple. The 48MP Main camera on #iPhone15Pro captures phenomenal detail of each camouflage.

1. 2. Kinabalu Gliding Gecko 
3. 4. Long-nosed Horn Frog 
5. 6. Mossy Stick Insect

Additional hardware and software used.
#ShotoniPhone by Chien C. Lee @chienleephotography

node.text: "Pink buildings are always cheerful." #ShotoniPhone by Laura G. @miamicolortheory

user.full_name: 円谷プロダクション

node.text:
Commissioned by Apple. Using iPhone 15 Pro’s Ultra Wide camera and low-light capabilities, the iconic Japanese superhero Ultraman and Kaiju monster Gomora come to life through the magic of #stopmotion

“Stop motion gives a voice to the still, telling stories in unexpected ways.” #ShotoniPhone by Animist @hannibalsaikaku

Additional software used.
Copyright permission from Tsuburaya Productions.
Rolling out Pink in the Big Apple. By Ian Padgham @origiful

Commissioned by Apple. The locals in Lop Buri, Thailand, hold a Monkey Buffet Festival every year in homage to its simian residents.

“It is the way the people and monkeys co-exist.

I want to tell the story of how monkeys interact with the food in their kingdom.” 

#ShotoniPhone by Un Wuthisak @un.factory01

Commissioned by Apple. Minuscule suit buttons. A shrunken snowplow. iPhone 15 Pro Max captured every stop-motion surprise in the holiday short film from Apple.

#ShotoniPhone by Anna M. @annamantzaris

Commissioned by Apple. Reaching 15 is worth celebrating. So @elweydelosperros decided to throw a one-of-a-kind party for a special quinceañera and her furry friends. There’s nothing more fitting to capture the fun than the new #iPhone15Pro. #ShotoniPhone

Commissioned by Apple. From the latest iPhone commercial, the iPhone 15 Pro captured portraits of the stars, the car chases, the stunts and all the explosions we could pack in a 60-second blockbuster.
“There’s no business like shooting heroic portraits of aliens and blowing up cars.”
#ShotoniPhone by Daniel Landin.

node.accessibility_caption: Black and white photo of a reflection of woman in a window with city scape.

node.text: Commissioned by Apple. “I trained in architecture so I enjoy locations that have a distinct character, that tells stories about the history and the spirit of a place.” #ShotoniPhone by Vivien L. @vdubl. Selections of Vivien’s photos on display at Salon Corderie in Paris.

node.text:
Commissioned by Apple. #Diwali sweets are edible works of art that celebrate life and delight the soul. #ShotoniPhone15

“Through still life imagery, I discover and capture the beauty of everyday objects.”

#ShotoniPhone by @porus.vimadalal 

Join Porus Vimadalal for a live session of Today at Apple on 14th, November at Apple BKC.

node.accessibility_caption: A car is parked on a dirt road surrounded by mountains. The cat is a convertible jeep, and a man stands inside of it looking at his surroundings.

An image of the same man sitting in the same car. The photo is taken from a low angle where we are looking up at him. One of his hands is holding onto the top of the windshield, while the other hand is holding binoculars that he’s looking through.
At nighttime, the same man is sitting in front of his parked car. The car has two bright headlights on, and he’s sitting between the two lights.
A close-up shot of a parrot's profile.

node.text: "I waited patiently for the birds to act as I imagined." #ShotoniPhone by Khairul S. @k__amin

node.accessibility_caption: A close-up shot of a parrot's profile.
An owl is perched on the edge of a large pot of water staring directly at the camera.
A heron with a long, orange-colored neck is shown looking toward the sky. The bird is very in-focus while the landscape is blurred behind it.
A white peacock stands with its back faced towards the camera though its tail-feathers are not spread. Its face is looking towards the right, and its crest resembles a sort of crown.
